message.raw:
Manually inspected 2to3 results to determine any code potentially in need
of attention.

More kosher version check in excepthook
list(dict) fix in excepthook

Explicit use of standard library configparser in labconfig in python2 so that
we don't depend on the backported configparser module (we can decide to do
so later if we want to start using Python3 features in the configparser
module while retaining backward compatbility but I doubt we will need this
before Python 2 compat is dropped anyway).

No more issues highlighted by inspection of 2to3 results.

message.raw:
Make qtwidgets require qtutils 2.1.0

Make properties be able to extract JSON properties regardless of whether they
are stored in the file as fixed length bytestrings or as variable length
unicode strings, and regardless of whether the device name is stored as either
type of string.

This frees the way for future labscript to save variable length
unicode strings, with all code still able to read both type of strings.

The image object returned by PyCapture

so that it occurs before changing
threads. This appears to have stopped
the program from getting seg faults.

message.raw:
Fix abort method

The abort method was not clearing bad images
from the results_queue, which caused blacs
and the camera server to desynchronize. Now,
the abort command will pull the bad images
out of the queue to keep the server in sync
with blacs.

DSB

out of the queue to keep the server in sync
with blacs.

Update Image Save

suggestion from DM. Testing indicates that this
method to convert from FLIR's image format to a
numpy array reduces saving time by 10-50% per
image (variation in improvement is probably due to
variation in saving time before improvement).

want to set black level on a per camera basis in the
future.

Adding PyCapture2 Camera Server to Bitbucket

This file contains a command line camera server for
Pointgrey/FLIR usb3 cameras. It optionally utilizes
the new acquistion_ROI property of the camera class.
To start the server, type "python PyCapture2_camera
_server.py <cameraNameFromBlacs>" in a command line
running in the labscript_utils directory.

DSB
